<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 6:21PM MDT  by NWS Aberdeen</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Campbell and northwestern McPherson Counties through 800 PM CDT...
At 721 PM CDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm near Eureka, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Greenway around 730 PM CDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
